wdi2-NY.GDP.COAL.RT.ZS.def: Coal rents are the difference between the value of both hard and soft coal production at world prices and their total costs of production.
wdi2-NY.GDP.COAL.RT.ZS.name: Coal rents
wdi2-NY.GDP.COAL.RT.ZS.source: World Bank staff estimates based on sources and methods described in the World Bank's The Changing Wealth of Nations.
